cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.SI 

The paper proposes a novel approach for automatic neuron discovery in deep neural networks, which is a topic closely related to machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). The experiments are conducted on image classification tasks (cs.CV) using popular network architectures (LeNet-5 and ResNet-20) and datasets (MNIST and CIFAR10), which are common in computer vision research. The approach involves learning activation functions for neurons, which is a topic related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and signal processing (cs.SI).
